<p>I want to find a way to do clean communication between my two sibling directives. I want to implement "insertAtCaret" functionality for a textarea in one directive, to be called from another.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;text-holder ng-model='model.text' /&gt; &lt;text-inserter&gt;     &lt;a ng-click='insert("hello")'&gt;Hello&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/text-inserter&gt; </code></pre>  <p><code>text-holder</code> turns into something like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class='my-class'&gt;     &lt;h3&gt;Enter some text:&lt;/h3&gt;     &lt;textarea ng-model='ngModel'&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt; &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The <code>text-inserter</code> needs to insert stuff into that <code>textarea</code> - what's the cleanest angular-ish way to allow that communication? I want to be able to support multiple instances of that on the page. Should I just create a unique id for each one from a shared service? It seems a little unclean.</p>